Medical service or product that utilizes a rate reimbursement technique. OMH organizes its Rate Codes into the following groups:
1. Partial Hospitalization;
2. Recovery Services (PMHP - Prepaid Mental Health Plan);
3. Targeted Case Management (Intensive Case Management “ICM”, BCM, SCM);
4. Home and Community Based Services Waiver (HCBS);
5. Clinic Treatment;
6. Comprehensive Psychiatric Emergency Program;
7. Community Residence;
8. Day Treatment;
9. Family Based Treatment/Teaching Family Home;
10. Psychiatric Inpatient OMH;
11. Assertive Community Treatment (“ACT”);
12. Continuing Day Treatment;
13. Intensive Psychiatric Rehabilitation Treatment;
14. Residential Treatment Facility;
15. Personalized Recovery Oriented Services.  Program type definitions can be found at http://bi.omh.state.ny.us/bridges/definitions#1810

